<figure typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:C_grammar_stmt2_svg.svg" class="mw-file-description"><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/C_grammar_stmt2_svg.svg/250px-C_grammar_stmt2_svg.svg.png" decoding="async" width="250" height="120" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a2/C_grammar_stmt2_svg.svg/500px-C_grammar_stmt2_svg.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="881" data-file-height="423" /></a><figcaption>Simplified excerpt of the formal grammar<sup id="cite&#95;ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span class="cite-bracket">&#91;</span>1<span class="cite-bracket">&#93;</span></a></sup> for the <a href="/wiki/C_(programming_language)" title="C (programming language)">C programming language</a> (left), and a derivation of a piece of C code (right) from the nonterminal symbol <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle \langle {\text{Stmt}}\rangle }">
