<p>of all terminal-symbol strings derivable from the start symbol.
</p><p>A language <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">L</span> is said to be a context-free language (CFL), if there exists a CFG <span class="texhtml mvar" style="font-style:italic;">G</span>, such that <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML"  alttext="{\displaystyle L=L(G)}">
